EditorData.CinematicNodeContext:
The planecaster vibrates, shaking the ground around it. 
Flares of light curl up in its centre and grow to full form. 
Vlaakith appears, awesome and terrible, at least twice the size of any human, a hologram in a haze of astral flares.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] The planecaster vibrates with energy and a hologram of Vlaakith forms
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] Flares of light curl up from the planecaster to form a Hologram of vlaakith.

Text.Value: As long as they live, the Prism is compromised.
Do as I say, and we feast in Tu'narath together.
Perhaps I misheard. You would not speak ill of a god. Would you?

EditorData.NodeContext: again, she's close to losing it a bit here, "would you" said with max venom

Text.Value: I spoke too hastily - please forgive me.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The image of Vlaakith flickers away within the planecaster, replaced by an image of the artefact suspended above the device.
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] Vlaakith flickers and is replaced by a hologram of the artefact

Text.Value: Insolent child. You are my subject. My word is law.
Obey, my child, and be forgiven.
Obey, and be forgiven.
Inquisitor W'wargaz was potent. We are impressed.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shot of player reacting to hearing a disembodied voice.
EditorData.NodeContext: Vlaakith should sligjhtly overpronounce every word, think Davros from Doctor Who, each syllable drips with a kind of mad, ancient evil
EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] Vlaakith's voice echoing through the room. The voice is disembodied and being heard pre-hologram.

Text.Value: Stay standing, exactly as you are.
YOU WISH TO SEE GODHOOD?
Vlaakith gha'g shkath zai!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The Inquisitor kneels before Vlaakith's image, surprised to see her. All of his staff kneel also.
EditorData.NodeContext: pronounced VLAH-kith gawg shkaath ZAI (meaning 'For the honour of Vlaakith!')

Text.Value: Do not leave this room before it is done, or I will undo you - you will be your queen's child no longer.
As you say, my Queen. I will slay the Prism's occupant.

EditorData.stateContext: The inquisitor and the other githyanki aside from players are kneeling

Text.Value: BLASPHEMING TONGUE.
There is someone inside. Their mind is warped, broken - a blight.
That 'weapon' you carry - the Astral Prism - it is corrupted.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith summons a floating hologram of the artefact and psionically spins it, toying with it.
EditorData.SFXTags: Magical swoooming and whooshes from holo-Vlaakith playing with holo-artefact
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] Vlaakith summons a floating hologram of the artefact

Text.Value: You walk a fine line, child. Tread carefully lest you fall.
You know me. How can it be?
You will do your duty - or be githyanki no longer.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith looks the player over, and gives a ghastly, frightening smile.

Text.Value: They are an agent of the Grand Design. Sent to sabotage the Astral Prism - our last defence against the return of the Illithid Empire.
SILENCE, W'wargaz.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: After he is rebuked, W'wargaz stands sulkily behind the player

Text.Value: No. I am not your servant to be commanded on whim.
The god-queen of my people cannot kill someone herself?
I just think a real god could kill whoever she wants.
Ch'mar, zal'a Vlaakith. You know me.

EditorData.NodeContext: cheh-MAR ZAL-ah VLAH-kith - Vlaakith's will above all

Text.Value: I Wish you to end.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: at the word "wish", Vlaakith invokes the most powerful, reality-bending magic of the multiverse. The Wish. her image shakes, as does the room around the players. we cut to gameplay, and they die .
EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] The room begins to shake as Vlaakith's image distorts
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] The room begins to shake as Vlaakith's image distorts

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith, unfazed in the least, motions everyone present to rise.l Everyone rises.

Text.Value: Excellent. A servant most willing.
Extend your fealty one step further, and you will be rewarded.
My Queen - shkath zai!
- and ascend.
W'wargaz. She will not leave this room until it is done.
I will not give it to you. This artefact is mine by rights.
You bear that which is mine. I presume you have come to return it. Lae'zel.
Be wary of the creature's lying tongue. Cut it out, if you must.
Remain on your feet.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Vlaakith, unfazed in the least, motions everyone present to rise.l Everyone rises.

Text.Value: Lae'zel - reject me and be undone. Serve, and we feast in Tu'narath together.
My queen. You honour me with your presence.
You are permitted to look upon me. You are invited to kneel.
No. It is not. To own something is to know it.
Kill them.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: With a close of her fist, the artefact hologram is shattered in mid-air in a burst of astral flare.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] The hologram of the artefact shatters into an astral flare as vlaakith closes her fist
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] The hologram of the artefact shatters into an astral flare as vlaakith closes her fist

Text.Value: As you say, my Queen.
Urlon of K'liir speaks most highly. As did Al'chaia before him.
So - it is found.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Shot of player reacting to hearing a disembodied voice.
EditorData.NodeContext: Vlaakith should sligjhtly overpronounce every word, think Davros from Doctor Who, each syllable drips with a kind of mad, ancient evil
EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] Vlaakith's voice echoing through the room. The voice is disembodied and being heard pre-hologram.

Text.Value: I shall cleanse it for you, my Queen. Tell me how.
I am at your command, my Queen. The artefact is yours.
*The goddess of your kin. The Queen of the Astral, the stillest of Seas. Vlaakith has risen.*
I shall cleanse it for you, my Queen. Tell me how.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: W'wargaz appeals to his queen, desperate to be given this twisted honour

Text.Value: Do this, and I will cleanse you. Do this -
Kneel in reverence to your queen.
Use the planecaster's power to enter the artefact.
You seek purity. I may yet grant it.
To honour me is to obey me. On your knees.
I can't do that. The person inside protects me from the Absolute.
Ascension? My queen. An honour gained, a burden borne. I will not waste a second.
Do as she asks. Kneel.

Synopsis: Laezel meets Vlaaktih as a hologram. Avatar can decide if she accepts her orders to kill the prisoner or refuse. In both cases, the planecaster is activated.If you refuse, Vlaakith orders the inquisitor if alive to kill you if you try to exit the room or theatens to hunt you down if he's already dead. Orphan Laezel automatically accepts Vlaakith's orders.
